  <!-- Best Suited For -->
  <div class="rounded-xl bg-teal-50 border border-teal-200 p-4 mb-8">
    <p class="text-xs font-bold text-teal-800 uppercase tracking-wide mb-1">Best Suited For</p>
    <p class="text-sm text-teal-700">Futures traders who want a straightforward, single-phase challenge with no time pressure, no monthly fees, and a 100% profit split once funded. Ideal for disciplined traders focused on CME markets.</p>
  </div>

  <!-- ═══════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════ -->
  <!-- CHALLENGE DETAILS                                               -->
  <!-- ═══════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════ -->
  <h3 class="text-lg font-bold text-slate-900 mb-3">Challenge Phase Details</h3>

  <p class="mb-3">
    To pass the FundedNext Futures Challenge, you need to reach a profit target while staying inside the daily and overall drawdown limits. You also need to trade consistently &mdash; if more than 40% of your profit comes from one big day, your target will be adjusted higher.
  </p>

  <p class="mb-3">
    You can trade both mini and micro contracts. Micros count as one-tenth of a mini, so if your cap is 3 mini contracts, you could instead trade up to 30 micros. This gives more flexibility over position sizing, especially for smaller accounts.
  </p>

  <p class="mb-3">
    The drawdown is trailing based on your end-of-day balance. Unrealized profits don't move the drawdown buffer &mdash; you need to close trades to lock in gains and raise the buffer.
  </p>

  <p class="mb-6">
    News trading is allowed during the challenge, and there's no restriction on how long you take. Once you hit the profit target and pass all rule checks, your challenge account is paused at the end of the trading day. After KYC, your funded account is issued.
  </p>

  <!-- To Pass -->
  <div class="space-y-3 mb-8">
    <div class="rounded-lg bg-slate-50 border border-slate-200 p-4">
      <p class="font-bold text-slate-900 mb-1">Profit Target</p>
      <p>Reach the required profit level based on your account size ($1,250 / $2,500 / $6,000).</p>
    </div>
    <div class="rounded-lg bg-slate-50 border border-slate-200 p-4">
      <p class="font-bold text-slate-900 mb-1">Drawdown Rules</p>
      <p>Stay within both daily and max trailing drawdown limits. Drawdown trails based on end-of-day balance.</p>
    </div>
    <div class="rounded-lg bg-slate-50 border border-slate-200 p-4">
      <p class="font-bold text-slate-900 mb-1">Consistency Rule</p>
      <p>No more than 40% of your profit target can come from a single day. If you exceed that, your target increases.</p>
    </div>
    <div class="rounded-lg bg-slate-50 border border-slate-200 p-4">
      <p class="font-bold text-slate-900 mb-1">Strategy Limits</p>
      <p>You must trade manually and avoid any prohibited tactics (automated trading, hedging across accounts, latency arbitrage).</p>
    </div>
  </div>

  <!-- ═══════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════ -->
  <!-- SCALING PLAN                                                    -->
  <!-- ═══════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════ -->
  <h3 class="text-lg font-bold text-slate-900 mb-3">Futures Account Scaling</h3>

  <p class="mb-3">
    When you pass the FundedNext Futures Challenge and receive a funded account, you unlock contract scaling. This feature lets you trade more contracts as you grow your account balance.
  </p>

  <p class="mb-4">
    Scaling happens automatically based on your end-of-day (EOD) balance. As your profits increase, FundedNext Futures raises the number of contracts you're allowed to trade.
  </p>

  <div class="overflow-x-auto rounded-xl border border-slate-200 mb-8">
    <table class="w-full text-sm whitespace-nowrap">
      <thead class="bg-slate-800 text-xs font-semibold text-white uppercase tracking-wide">
        <tr>
          <th class="px-4 py-3 text-left">Account Size</th>
          <th class="px-4 py-3 text-left">EOD Balance Range</th>
          <th class="px-4 py-3 text-center">Max Contracts Allowed</th>
        </tr>
      </thead>
      <tbody class="divide-y divide-slate-100">
        <tr class="bg-white">
          <td class="px-4 py-3 font-semibold text-slate-900" rowspan="2">$25,000</td>
          <td class="px-4 py-3 text-slate-700">Below $1,500</td>
          <td class="px-4 py-3 text-center text-slate-900">2 mini / 20 micro</td>
        </tr>
        <tr class="bg-slate-50">
